(588, 'UFCW Local 480', '<p style="margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 25.2000007629395px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(132, 137, 140);"><img alt="" src="http://www.ufcwunitedlatinos.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/P7250022-e1426700093417.jpg" style="height: 210px; width: 280px;" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 25.2000007629395px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(132, 137, 140);">United Food and Commercial Workers Local 480&nbsp;is a 2,500 member labor union based in Honolulu, Hawaii. The local is a progressive voice in the labor movement and the community with a strong tradition of member advocacy and involvement. It is an affiliate of the United Food and Commercial Workers International union based in Washington DC.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 25.2000007629395px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(132, 137, 140);">Local 480&nbsp;members work primarily in retail grocery and meat and in nursing homes,&nbsp;retail drug stores, agriculture and food processing, wholesale meat, seafood processing,&nbsp;and in the industry of education.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 25.2000007629395px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(132, 137, 140);">Wherever Local 480&nbsp;members work, they have a strong voice on the job.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 25.2000007629395px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(132, 137, 140);">Local 480&nbsp;policy is set by its&nbsp;member executive board which consists of its elected officers and rank and file members. Members from many of the Hawaiian Islands&nbsp;sit on its board. The activism of the board and the union&rsquo;s membership assures the democratic nature of the organization and perpetuate its progressive tradition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 25.2000007629395px; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(132, 137, 140);">Local 480 is a Union Preparing Today for the Needs of its Members Tomorrow.</p>\r\n', '', '2015-03-26 11:07:51', '40.1', 6, '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 0),
