(604, 'A Message from President Pete Maturino', '<p style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px;"><img alt="" src="http://www.ufcwunitedlatinos.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Pete-M-1.jpg" style="width: 280px; height: 269px;" /></p>\r\n\r\n<div id="hdr" style="margin: 0px 0px 10px; padding: 10px; outline: none; border-width: 10px 0px 0px; border-top-style: solid; border-top-color: rgb(0, 37, 87); font-family: inherit; font-size: 16px; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; overflow: hidden; background: rgb(0, 73, 144);">\r\n<header class="wrapper" id="hdr-content" style="margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px; outline: none; max-width: 980px;">\r\n<h1 class="pagetitle" style="line-height: 1em; margin: 0px 12px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none; border: 0px; font-family: proxima-nova-condensed, proxima-nova, ''Proxima Nova'', HelveticaNeue, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 1.875em; vertical-align: baseline; font-stretch: normal; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); float: left;">United Latinos of UFCW</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="post" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-size: 16px; font-style: inherit; font-weight: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<div class="entry" style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px 0px 1.5em; outline: none; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n<h2 style="line-height: 1em; margin: 20px 0px 10px; padding: 18px 0px 10px 20px; outline: none; border-width: 10px 0px 1px; border-top-style: solid; border-bottom-style: dotted; border-top-color: rgb(255, 196, 37); border-bottom-color: rgb(0, 73, 144); font-family: proxima-nova-condensed, proxima-nova, ''Proxima Nova'', HelveticaNeue, ''Helvetica Neue'', Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 1.875em; vertical-align: baseline; font-stretch: normal; color: rgb(0, 73, 144); min-height: 30px; background-image: url(http://www.ufcwaction.org/wp-content/themes/ufcw/images/bg_hdr.png); background-attachment: initial; background-size: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-position: 0% 22px; background-repeat: no-repeat;">A message from&nbsp;UFCW United Latinos President Pete Maturino</h2>\r\n\r\n<div><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px; font-size: 13px;">On November 20, 2014 President Obama took a step forward in completing part of a promise to the Latino community and more importantly to the immigrant community all over this country. It is my belief that we should embrace this effort by the President to attempt to fix dysfunctional immigration system and begin the process of helping and or assisting the membership of this Union in completing the application and forms needed to receive the deferred action.</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px; font-size: 13px;">One of the most important things we as union officials, whether working through the local union or in partnership with community agency&rsquo;s, is to get the word out to the immigrant community to be very careful of those individuals who&rsquo;s only goal is to take your money and leave you with nothing done.</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px; font-size: 13px;">Along with this letter I am attaching information from the National Immigration Law Center on what is believed the law will do and what it means to millions of immigrants, as well as ways the immigrant community can prepare when the applications become available for processing, I hope this will help you in your efforts in helping members through this process.</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px; font-size: 13px;">The United Latinos with help of the International and Esther Lopez from the Civil Rights department will be able to assist the immigrant community within our Union not only in providing updated information on changes that may come up in the Presidents directive, but beginning in early December if anyone of you who has a group of members that you feel would benefit from a presentation from the Civil Rights Department on this deferred action, you can contact the United Latinos to make those arrangements.</span></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div><span style="font-family: Georgia, ''Times New Roman'', ''Bitstream Charter'', Times, serif; line-height: 19px; font-size: 13px;">At minimum if there is anything that you feel you need from the Civil Rights Department in order to assist you members on this deferred actio</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', '', '2015-03-25 17:12:02', '34', 2, '', '', '', '', '', NULL, 0),
